## Unit I — Container Fundamentals

### Q1. Launch an Apache httpd container on port 8085
```powershell
docker pull httpd:alpine
docker images
docker run -d --name httpd-demo -p 8085:80 httpd:alpine
docker ps
curl.exe http://localhost:8085
```
**Open in browser:** http://localhost:8085

### Q2. Serve a custom message from an Apache container
```powershell
docker run -d --name html-test -p 8082:80 httpd:alpine
docker exec html-test sh -c "echo '<h1>EXPLORING DOCKER CONTAINERS</h1>' > /usr/local/apache2/htdocs/index.html"
curl.exe http://localhost:8082
docker stop html-test; docker rm html-test
```

### Q3. Start a MongoDB container with port forwarding
```powershell
# Map host port 27018 to container port 27017
docker run -d --name mongo-instance -p 27018:27017 mongo:7
docker ps
```

### Q4. Show all Docker object categories
```powershell
docker images      # List images
docker ps -a       # List all containers
docker network ls  # List networks
docker volume ls   # List volumes
```

