## Unit II — Dockerfile & Networking

### Q5. Build and launch a custom Node.js application
```powershell
cd labs\unit-2-dockerfile
docker build -t node-app-demo:1.0 .
docker run -d --name node-demo -p 3001:3000 node-app-demo:1.0
curl.exe http://localhost:3001
```

### Q6. Set up a custom network and link containers
```powershell
docker network create services-net
docker run -d --name redis --network services-net redis:alpine
docker run -it --rm --network services-net alpine ping -c 3 redis
```

### Q7. Use a named volume for data persistence
```powershell
docker volume create appdata
docker run -d -v appdata:/data --name storage-test alpine sleep 3600
docker exec storage-test sh -c "echo persistent > /data/file.txt"
docker rm -f storage-test
docker run --rm -v appdata:/data alpine cat /data/file.txt
```

### Q8. Extract a file from a container to the Windows Desktop
```powershell
docker run -d --name helper nginx:alpine
docker exec helper sh -c "mkdir -p /project && echo 'Practicing Docker Commands' > /project/notes.txt"
docker cp helper:/project/notes.txt "$env:USERPROFILE\Desktop\notes.txt"
docker rm -f helper
```

### Q9. Push an image to GitHub Container Registry
```powershell
docker build -t ghcr.io/YOUR_USERNAME/myapp:1.0 .
docker login ghcr.io -u YOUR_USERNAME
# Enter your GitHub Personal Access Token when prompted
docker push ghcr.io/YOUR_USERNAME/myapp:1.0
```

