## Unit VI — Jenkins

### Q15. Set up Jenkins on Windows using Docker
```powershell
docker volume create jenkins_data
docker run -d -p 8083:8080 -p 50001:50000 `
  -v jenkins_data:/var/jenkins_home `
  --name jenkins-server jenkins/jenkins:lts
docker exec jenkins-server cat /var/jenkins_home/secrets/initialAdminPassword
```
**Open in browser:** http://localhost:8083

### Q16. Standard Jenkins pipeline stages
1. Checkout (pull from Git)
2. Build (Maven/npm compile)
3. Test (Surefire/JUnit execution)
4. Package (create JAR or Docker image)
5. Deploy (push to SSH/cloud target)
6. Post (notifications and cleanup)

